# Challenges

Email Intelligence investigations may face several challenges:

* Private email addresses are not publicly indexed.
* Multiple individuals may have similar email usernames.
* Public information can become outdated.
* Some websites restrict indexing.
* Search results may require verification.

These challenges highlight the importance of patience and cross-verification.


# Best Practices

When performing Email Intelligence investigations:

* Work only with publicly available information.
* Verify findings using multiple trusted sources.
* Respect privacy and applicable laws.
* Avoid making assumptions.
* Document findings carefully.
* Use OSINT techniques responsibly.


# Common Mistakes

Common mistakes beginners make include:

* Depending on a single OSINT tool.
* Assuming every result belongs to the same individual.
* Ignoring verification.
* Misinterpreting breach information.
* Collecting unnecessary personal information.


